align=top align=left class=m><span class=title> did you offer cash?</span><hr size=1> i have a 57 druid and a 52 paladin, and my druid is VERY desensitized to port requests<br><br>maybe if you offer 50++ pp you'll get some responses, otherwise most lv50+ druids really dont care <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ucylria.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cylria</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wandering Knight</span><br>  Posts: 157<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/16/02 9:09:12 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: did you offer cash?</span><hr size=1> You'd think with our increased ability to rez, we would become more sympathetic to all the begging.<br><br>Oh, please! Please! Let me drop everything to run to where ever you are and be your personal taxi.<br><br>If you want a port, do this:<br>-If possible go to a druid ring or Wizard spire/pyramid, and offer to pay any druids or wizards there for a port. Those are most likely to be the ones currently porting for cash and will give you the best price.<br>-If reaching a spire/ring isn't practical, send a polite tell to any non-anon druids or wizards, once again with your request and a payment offer.<br>-if both of those fail, then approach an anon druid (prefably a soloer) and make the same offer.<br><br>Standing in a zone and shouting is a terrible way to get what you want, this includes ports, rezzes, and groups. Confront people directly, be polite, and be willing to except NO for an answer. Sometimes people (including druids) just want to get something done. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukindreth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kindreth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wandering Knight</span><br>  Posts: 135<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/16/02 9:20:22 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://home.earthlink.net/~acastillo1/Images/EQ/knight.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: did you offer cash?</span><hr size=1> lol, you got feet go run your arse there =P<br><br>Just because druids got ports doesnt mean they have to port you. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usenchy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Senchy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Blessed Protector</span><br>  Posts: 402<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/16/02 9:22:13 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Druids Again</span><hr size=1> I don't think you can associate willingness-to-drop-what-you-do-to-port-people with a-class-does-not-need-upgrades. =) You just personally don't like druids.<br><br>When I play a druid I ignore port requests too for notable exceptions and that's when I have nothing planned/to-do. (No, not for money since there is nothing buyable left for my pally)<br><br>Druids need some help with grouping at certain levels for indoor encounters, otherwise they are strong already. Maybe give them an indoor only spells that will not strengthen their outdoor power. Currently the most-commonly-only reason people add random druids to there group is the need for snare, not the healin/nuking/buffing power. <br> <br> <p>Senchy Solariatus <BR>60 Crusader of Rodcet Nife<BR>56 Chanter of Rodcet Nife (Tymbor)<BR>Dol Amroth<BR><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=79641>Typical Raid Setup</a><BR><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=66884>AC Solo Gear</a><BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubeldukil.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Beldukil</A></span><br> <span 